reviews.comment: I have owned and driven this car for over 10 years now. Apart from tyres and brakes I have only had a broken spring on 2 occasions. I still love my car after all this time, feels like you are driving a safe quality car. It is also very good on fuel & cheap to insure. Suits me to a T. The only thing I would change would be the number of doors, next car will b a four door, hope it get another 2 year from it before I need to buy another car. Would definitely consider buying another A1 if my budget can afford it

A little beauty that stands out in a crowd wherever she goes. Had her seven years now and looks as good as new! Serviced regularly and never given any trouble. The only other costs to date being new tyres. Great build quality compared to other "tinny" makes. No road tax either!

Had problems with the car since new. Suspension squeezed every time someone got in the car for the first six months. Rear light cluster accumulated about 3 to 4 Centimetres of water every time it was outside in the rain. More recently as a five year old car I have had since new and all service and MOT work done at an Audio. dealership I have had problems I did not expect. Small things such as a very rarely used passenger visor clip breaking, the petrol cap cover breaking and a flap motor behind the glove box for the ventilation breaking and making a noise every time I turn on the ignition. £150 for the petrol cover to be fixed as they have to replace the complete housing. Quoted £502 to repair the ventilation motor which I understand the part cost about £80. They are great at repairing things during the warranty but take you to the cleaners after that.
